  <div class="page-header">
    <h1 class="page-title">Parameter Sensitivity</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Environmental conditions are rarely static or precisely known. A robust engineering model
      requires sensitivity analysis to understand which input parameters dominate the system's behavior.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p style="font-size:14px;color:#374151;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:12px;">
    We perturb the key independent variables by ±20% from their baseline values and measure the
    resulting change in the final state variables at t = 168 hours. The parameters of highest interest are:
  </p>
  <ul style="font-size:14px;color:#374151;line-height:2;padding-left:22px;margin-bottom:36px;">
    <li><strong>Wind Speed (W)</strong> — directly drives evaporation mass transfer and wave-induced emulsification.</li>
    <li><strong>Temperature (T)</strong> — strongly dictates the evaporation rate.</li>
    <li><strong>Initial Volume (V_s)</strong> — dictates slick thickness and total spreading area.</li>
    <li><strong>Oil Density (ρ_o)</strong> — influences gravity-driven spreading.</li>
  </ul>

